column3: Well, well, what have we here? I thought I knew all the prominent trades<If(PlayerParameter(4))>women<Else/>men</If> who pass through Solution Nine. Come to sign a contract, I trust?

You needn't fuss yourself over the details─the arrangement is blissfully simple. You provide me with product, and I compensate you for said product with scrips. A <If(PlayerParameter(4))>woman<Else/>man</If> of your expertise must surely recognize such a lucrative offer when they hear one.
In truth, it was the Turali who first introduced me to the many conveniences of trade with scrips. A system brought to them by a tradeswoman by the name of Rowena. But that is neither here nor there.
You will be well paid for your contributions─with scrips, naturally─and your earnings can in turn be used to purchase any of our wares that strike your fancy. So, what do you say?
Splendid! Simply splendid. And lest you worry, there will be no quotas to speak of. You need only make deliveries when inspiration strikes!
Here's to a most beautiful and profitable partnership! I very much look forward to doing business with you.
<sigh> What I wouldn't give for a capable trades<If(PlayerParameter(4))>woman<Else/>man</If>. Now how am I to move all this merchandise?
In order to undertake this quest, you must be a Disciple of the Hand or the Land of level 90 or above.
